There are a few alternatives here:

* Move the sexpLibrary to a `deps` (dependencies) directory at the same level as `include` or `src`. Then, the checker will not complain.
* Tweak code_check.sh to ignore the warnings/errors on the sexpLibrary using the SUPRESS variable.

Hi Nima, I am working on integrating your action parser to the rest of the code base. My current progress can be seen in the branch jliang_model.

Could you take a look at it, and make the following changes:

1)Make it so that when update() is called, it updates the member variable action.hingeJoints for the each agent.

2) Use the typedef defined in Agent.hh called AgentId instead of initmsg. 

3) Call the addagent and removeagent functions in gamestate when you receive an init or disconnect.
content.html:
Hi Nima, I am working on integrating your action parser to the rest of the code base. My current progress can be seen in the branch jliang_model.

Could you take a look at it, and make the following changes:

1)Make it so that when update() is called, it updates the member variable action.hingeJoints for the each agent.

2) Use the typedef defined in Agent.hh called AgentId instead of initmsg.

3) Call the addagent and removeagent functions in gamestate when you receive an init or disconnect.

This is a Effector class. It uses the Server class architecture and implemented its Parse(). Retrieving effectors values form messages has been implemented using s-expression library. The description of data structures, accessors and methods can be found in EffectorParser.hh.

Also, effector messages that are used in Simspark simulator can be found in following link:
[http://simspark.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Effectors](http://simspark.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Effectors)
